<task id="023" project="sdap-bff-api-and-performance-enhancement-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Persistent analysis state — Dataverse durable layer</title>
    <tags>bff-api, dataverse, resilience</tags>
    <phase>3.2</phase>
    <estimate>4h</estimate>
    <status>pending</status>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <dependencies>022</dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    <goal>Add Dataverse durable write (async fire-and-forget with retry) as persistence layer behind Redis.</goal>
    <context>Task 022 added Redis as the hot layer for analysis results. This task adds Dataverse as the durable persistence layer. Writes to Dataverse are async fire-and-forget with retry — they must not block the request. The dual-write pattern is: Redis (fast, synchronous) + Dataverse (durable, asynchronous). On Redis miss, Dataverse serves as the fallback read source. A feature flag controls whether durable persistence is active.</context>
    <constraints>
      - Dataverse write must be async fire-and-forget — must not block the request path
      - Retry logic for Dataverse writes (transient failures)
      - Dual-write: Redis (sync, fast) + Dataverse (async, durable)
      - Feature flag: Analysis:Persistence:Enabled (default: true)
      - Analysis must survive BFF restart — SC-09 verification
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file path=".claude/constraints/data.md" reason="Dataverse data access constraints" />
      <file path=".claude/patterns/dataverse/entity-operations.md" reason="Entity CRUD operation patterns" />
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step id="1">Verify sprk_analysisresult entity schema in Dataverse — confirm fields for analysis state storage</step>
    <step id="2">Implement async Dataverse write with fire-and-forget pattern and retry logic for transient failures</step>
    <step id="3">Wire dual-write into AnalysisStateCacheService: Redis (fast, sync) + Dataverse (durable, async)</step>
    <step id="4">Implement Dataverse fallback read when Redis miss — warm result back into Redis</step>
    <step id="5">Add feature flag Analysis:Persistence:Enabled (default: true) to control durable writes</step>
    <step id="6">Integration test: write analysis state → simulate restart → verify recovery from Dataverse</step>
    <step id="7">Run dotnet test — verify all tests pass</step>
  </steps>
  <outputs>
    <artifact>Updated src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Caching/AnalysisStateCacheService.cs with dual-write</artifact>
    <artifact>Updated appsettings.json with Analysis:Persistence:Enabled flag</artifact>
  </outputs>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Dual-write working: Redis (sync) + Dataverse (async fire-and-forget with retry)</criterion>
    <criterion>Analysis state survives BFF restart — recoverable from Dataverse</criterion>
    <criterion>Feature flag Analysis:Persistence:Enabled controls durable writes</criterion>
    <criterion>Dataverse write does not block request path</criterion>
    <criterion>SC-09 (analysis survives restart) verified via integration test</criterion>
    <criterion>dotnet test passes with no regressions</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
